ion in 1993 there appeared important new contributions, like the solutions of two different affine Bernstein conjectures, due to Chern and Calabi, respectively. Moreover, a large subclass of hyperbolic affine spheres were classified in recent years, namely the locally strongly convex Blaschke hypersurfaces that have parallel cubic form with respect to the Levi-Civita connection of the Blaschke metric. The authors of this book present such results and new methods of proof.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGlobal differential geometry. 0aHypersurfaces. 4aAffine differential geometry. 4aGlobal differential geometry. 4aHypersurface. 7aMATHEMATICS / Geometry / Differential.2bisacsh  aAffine differential geometry.  aGlobal differential geometry.  aHypersurfaces.1 aHu, Zejun, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSimon, Udo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZhao, Guosong, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Expositions in Mathematics Backlist eBook Packagez978311049496908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2015z9783110438765oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831103909020 cprintz978311026667240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311026889840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110268898423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110268898.jpg  a978-3-11-049496-9  DG Expositions in Mathematics Backlist eBook Package  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA